@NODE Introduction
@TITLE "Screen Recorder · Introduction"


    @{b}Introduction@{ub}


    Screen Recorder is a small utility to record videos from
    your screens.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements
@TITLE "Screen Recorder · Requirements"


    @{b}Requirements@{ub}

    Minimum requirements for Classic OS

     * 68020 with FPU
     * Kickstart 2.0
     * CyberGraphics 3.0
     * MUI 3.0
     * 4MB RAM
     * asyncio.library (http://aminet.net/dev/c/AsyncIO.lha)


   Minimum requirements (MorphOS)

    * MorphOS 1 with Update Pack #1

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@TITLE "Screen Recorder · Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy the drawer to a place you like.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CLI
@TITLE "Screen Recorder · Command line options"


    @{b}Command line options@{ub}


    The command line template is
    RECORD/S,HIDE/S,VIDEOFORMAT/K,FRAMERATE/K,SCALING/K,QUALITY/K

    where

    RECORD      - Starts recording immediately
    VIDEOFORMAT - Set video format, must be either MJPEG or MNG
    FRAMERATE   - Set recording frame rate, supported options are:
                  Normal, Half speed, Quarter speed, 10 fps, 5 fps, 1 fps
    SCALING     - Set scaling, supported options are:
                  No scaling, Half size, Quarter size, 1024x768, 800x600,
                  640x480, 320x240, 160x120
    QUALITY     - Set quality level, supported options are:
                  Best, Excellent, Good, Poor, Bad

@ENDNODE

@NODE REXX
@TITLE "Screen Recorder · REXX"


    @{b}REXX@{ub}


    Following REXX commands are recognized:

    RECORD            - Starts recording immediately
    VIDEO FORMAT/K    - Set video format, must be either MJPEG or MNG
    FRAMERATE SPEED/K - Set recording frame rate, supported options are:
                        Normal, Half speed, Quarter speed, 10 fps, 5 fps, 1 fps
    SCALING SIZE/K    - Set scaling, supported options are:
                        No scaling, Half size, Quarter size, 1024x768, 800x600,
                        640x480, 320x240, 160x120
    QUALITY LEVEL/K   - Set quality level, supported options are:
                        Best, Excellent, Good, Poor, Bad


@ENDNODE

